Look at a linear model using the variables that were identified by VSURF, plus interactions that seem biologically meaningful

Structure data for LM

Normalize function

normalize <- function(x) {
    return ((x - mean(x)) / sd(x))
  }

Filter and normalize

LMdf <- df %>% 
  mutate(sqrt_shrubarea3 = sqrt(shrubarea3)) %>%
  mutate(log_shrubarea3 = log(shrubarea3)) %>% 
  dplyr::select(Fire, Sdlg, heatload, Years, BasDia2016.cm, shrubarea3, sqrt_shrubarea3, log_shrubarea3, Elevation, Ht_cm1, Slope.Deg, Year, Aspect.rad.fold.NESW, incidrad) %>% 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, normalize) %>% 
  mutate(VertGrowth_Rel = df$VertGrowth_Rel)
LMdf <- droplevels(LMdf)

LME model using VSURF var results

Convert vars to formula structure

vars_one <- paste(vars, collapse = " + ")
vars_one
## [1] "heatload + Years + Aspect.rad.fold.NESW + Ht_cm1 + incidrad + sqrt_shrubarea3 + Elevation"
f <- formula(paste("VertGrowth_Rel ~ ",vars_one))
f
## VertGrowth_Rel ~ heatload + Years + Aspect.rad.fold.NESW + Ht_cm1 + 
##     incidrad + sqrt_shrubarea3 + Elevation

Run lme model

LM <- lme(f, data = LMdf, random = ~ 1| Fire/Sdlg, method = "ML")

Check collinearity - use vif from car pkg because in pines it was the same as the Zuur code

vif(LM)
##             heatload                Years Aspect.rad.fold.NESW 
##            12.341542             5.505169             7.089797 
##               Ht_cm1             incidrad      sqrt_shrubarea3 
##             1.788915             3.341943             1.256274 
##            Elevation 
##             2.823294

A VIF cutoff value of 5 is often used, and heatload has a GVIF much higher than that, so take it out and run the model again:

vars <- vars[vars != "heatload"]
vars_one <- paste(vars, collapse = " + ")
f <- update(as.formula(f), ~ . - heatload) 
LM <- lme(f, data = LMdf, random = ~ 1| Fire/Sdlg, method = "ML")

Repeat vif test

vif(LM)
##                Years Aspect.rad.fold.NESW               Ht_cm1 
##             4.557313             3.231299             1.703784 
##             incidrad      sqrt_shrubarea3            Elevation 
##             2.063094             1.242633             2.587283

Now everything looks ok.

See whether model with or without interaction is better

vars_int <- paste(vars_one, "+ Ht_cm1:sqrt_shrubarea3")
f_int <- formula(paste("VertGrowth_Rel ~ ",vars_int))
LM_int <- lme(f_int, data = LMdf, random = ~ 1| Fire/Sdlg, method = "ML")
AIC(LM)
## [1] 646.9281
AIC(LM_int)
## [1] 648.7291
if(
  AIC(LM) > AIC(LM_int)
) print(paste("WITH INTERACTION WINS BY", round(AIC(LM)-AIC(LM_int), digits = 2), "AIC")) else print(paste("WITHOUT INTERACTION WINS BY", round(AIC(LM_int)-AIC(LM), digits = 2)))
## [1] "WITHOUT INTERACTION WINS BY 1.8"

No difference, so Ill leave out the interaction

Find the shrubarea values associated with each quartile, and the mean growth for each of those

summary <- summary(sqrt(df$shrubarea3))
summary
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##   88.87  216.79  265.16  264.31  297.41  427.10
quart1 <- summary[2]
quart3 <- summary[5]
median <- summary[3]
min <- summary[1]
max <- summary[6]
mean <- mean(sqrt(df$shrubarea3))

fit_quart1 <- effects_df[which.min(abs(effects_df$sqrt_shrubarea3 - quart1)),]$fit
fit_quart1
## [1] -2.068827
fit_quart3 <- effects_df[which.min(abs(effects_df$sqrt_shrubarea3 - quart3)),]$fit
fit_median <- effects_df[which.min(abs(effects_df$sqrt_shrubarea3 - median)),]$fit

fit_min <- effects_df[which.min(abs(effects_df$sqrt_shrubarea3 - min)),]$fit
fit_max <- effects_df[which.min(abs(effects_df$sqrt_shrubarea3 - max)),]$fit
fit_mean <- effects_df[which.min(abs(effects_df$sqrt_shrubarea3 - mean)),]$fit

print(paste("fit_quart1 = ", exp(fit_quart1)))
## [1] "fit_quart1 =  0.126333886654464"

## [1] "fit_median =  0.133343543752151"

Plot effects of shrubarea

ggplot(effects_df)+
  geom_line(aes(x = sqrt_shrubarea3, y = exp(fit)))+
  geom_ribbon(aes(x = sqrt_shrubarea3, ymin = exp(lower), ymax = exp(upper)), alpha = .5, fill = "#fdbb84")+
  theme_bw()+
  xlab(bquote(
    (sqrt(`cover (cm)`%*%`height (cm)`))            
    ))+
#  xlab(bquote((sqrt(`cover (cm)`%*%`height (cm)`)))+
  ylab("Relative growth rate")+
 # ggtitle("Fir growth in relation to shrub environment within 2 m")+
  geom_rug(data = df, aes(x = sqrt(shrubarea3), y = exp(VertGrowth_Rel)), alpha = .5, position = "jitter", sides = "b")+
  ylim(c(0.04,0.3))+
  theme(
    #panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    #panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
    text = element_text(size = 11))
